# Heaps & Priority Queues Cheat Sheet

## 1. Core Concepts
- **Heap**: complete binary tree satisfying the heap property
- **Min-heap**: parent <= children. Root = minimum element.
- **Max-heap**: parent >= children. Root = maximum element.
- **Priority Queue**: abstract data type — heap is the standard implementation
- Stored as array: parent of i is `floor((i-1)/2)`, children are `2i+1` and `2i+2`

```typescript
// JS has no built-in heap — simulate with sorted array (inefficient) or implement
// MinHeap implementation
class MinHeap {
  private heap: number[] = [];
  private swap(i: number, j: number) { [this.heap[i],this.heap[j]]=[this.heap[j],this.heap[i]]; }
  push(val: number): void {
    this.heap.push(val);
    this.bubbleUp(this.heap.length-1);
  }
  pop(): number|undefined {
    if (this.heap.length===0) return undefined;
    this.swap(0, this.heap.length-1);
    const min = this.heap.pop()!;
    this.sinkDown(0);
    return min;
  }
  peek(): number { return this.heap[0]; }
  size(): number { return this.heap.length; }
  private bubbleUp(i: number): void {
    while (i > 0) {
      const parent = Math.floor((i-1)/2);
      if (this.heap[parent] <= this.heap[i]) break;
      this.swap(parent, i); i = parent;
    }
  }
  private sinkDown(i: number): void {
    const n = this.heap.length;
    while (true) {
      let smallest = i;
      const l = 2*i+1, r = 2*i+2;
      if (l < n && this.heap[l] < this.heap[smallest]) smallest = l;
      if (r < n && this.heap[r] < this.heap[smallest]) smallest = r;
      if (smallest === i) break;
      this.swap(i, smallest); i = smallest;
    }
  }
}
```

## 2. Top-K Problems
```typescript
// Kth Largest Element (LC 215) — min-heap of size k
function findKthLargest(nums: number[], k: number): number {
  // Simulate with sorted — in production use real min-heap
  const heap: number[] = [];
  for (const n of nums) {
    heap.push(n);
    heap.sort((a,b)=>a-b);
    if (heap.length > k) heap.shift();
  }
  return heap[0]; // root of min-heap = kth largest
}
// Top K Frequent Words (LC 692)
// 1. Build frequency map O(n)
// 2. Push all (freq, word) to max-heap
// 3. Pop k times
```

## 3. Merge K Sorted Lists/Arrays
```typescript
// Merge K sorted arrays using min-heap
// Each element in heap: [value, arrayIndex, elementIndex]
function mergeKSorted(arrays: number[][]): number[] {
  // Simulate with array — use real min-heap by value
  const result: number[] = [];
  const heap: [number,number,number][] = [];
  for (let i=0;i<arrays.length;i++)
    if (arrays[i].length) heap.push([arrays[i][0],i,0]);
  heap.sort((a,b)=>a[0]-b[0]);
  while (heap.length) {
    heap.sort((a,b)=>a[0]-b[0]);
    const [val,ai,ei] = heap.shift()!;
    result.push(val);
    if (ei+1<arrays[ai].length) heap.push([arrays[ai][ei+1],ai,ei+1]);
  }
  return result;
}
```

## 4. Two-Heap Pattern (Median)
```typescript
// Find Median from Data Stream (LC 295)
class MedianFinder {
  private lo: number[] = []; // max-heap (lower half) — negate for max
  private hi: number[] = []; // min-heap (upper half)
  private pushMax(heap: number[], val: number) {
    heap.push(-val); heap.sort((a,b)=>a-b);
  }
  private popMax(heap: number[]): number {
    heap.sort((a,b)=>a-b); return -heap.shift()!;
  }
  addNum(num: number): void {
    this.pushMax(this.lo, num);
    // Balance: largest of lo must be <= smallest of hi
    this.hi.push(this.popMax(this.lo)); this.hi.sort((a,b)=>a-b);
    if (this.lo.length < this.hi.length)
      this.pushMax(this.lo, this.hi.shift()!);
  }
  findMedian(): number {
    if (this.lo.length > this.hi.length) return -this.lo[0];
    return (-this.lo[0] + this.hi[0]) / 2;
  }
}
```

## 5. Complexity Table
| Operation | Binary Heap | Sorted Array |
|-----------|-------------|-------------|
| Insert (push) | O(log n) | O(n) |
| Extract min/max (pop) | O(log n) | O(1) |
| Peek min/max | O(1) | O(1) |
| Search | O(n) | O(log n) |
| Build from n elements | O(n) | O(n log n) |
| Decrease key | O(log n) | O(n) |

## 6. Common Heap Patterns
| Pattern | Heap Type | Example |
|---------|-----------|----------|
| Kth largest | Min-heap size k | LC 215 |
| Kth smallest | Max-heap size k | LC 378 |
| Top K elements | Min or max heap | LC 347 |
| Sliding window median | Two heaps | LC 480 |
| Merge K sorted | Min-heap | LC 23 |
| Task scheduling | Max-heap | LC 621 |

## 7. Gotchas
- Min-heap root = minimum; to simulate max-heap in JS, negate values
- `buildHeap` from array is O(n) using Floyd's heapify — NOT O(n log n)
- After pop, place last element at root and sink down (don't re-heap)
- Kth largest → min-heap of size k (root = kth largest)
- Kth smallest → max-heap of size k (root = kth smallest)
- Two heaps median: lo (max-heap) ≥ hi (min-heap), sizes differ by at most 1

# Sorting & Searching Cheat Sheet

## 1. Core Sorting Algorithms
```typescript
// Quicksort — O(n log n) average, O(n²) worst, O(log n) space
function quicksort(arr: number[], lo=0, hi=arr.length-1): void {
  if (lo >= hi) return;
  const pivot = partition(arr, lo, hi);
  quicksort(arr, lo, pivot-1);
  quicksort(arr, pivot+1, hi);
}
function partition(arr: number[], lo: number, hi: number): number {
  const pivot = arr[hi];
  let i = lo - 1;
  for (let j = lo; j < hi; j++) {
    if (arr[j] <= pivot) { i++; [arr[i],arr[j]]=[arr[j],arr[i]]; }
  }
  [arr[i+1],arr[hi]]=[arr[hi],arr[i+1]];
  return i+1;
}

// Mergesort — O(n log n) guaranteed, O(n) space, stable
function mergesort(arr: number[]): number[] {
  if (arr.length <= 1) return arr;
  const mid = Math.floor(arr.length/2);
  const left = mergesort(arr.slice(0,mid));
  const right = mergesort(arr.slice(mid));
  return merge(left, right);
}
function merge(l: number[], r: number[]): number[] {
  const res: number[] = [];
  let i=0, j=0;
  while (i<l.length && j<r.length) res.push(l[i]<=r[j] ? l[i++] : r[j++]);
  return [...res, ...l.slice(i), ...r.slice(j)];
}
```

## 2. Binary Search
```typescript
// Classic binary search — find exact target
function binarySearch(nums: number[], target: number): number {
  let lo=0, hi=nums.length-1;
  while (lo<=hi) {
    const mid = lo + Math.floor((hi-lo)/2);
    if (nums[mid]===target) return mid;
    else if (nums[mid]<target) lo=mid+1;
    else hi=mid-1;
  }
  return -1;
}
// Find left boundary (first occurrence / lower bound)
function lowerBound(nums: number[], target: number): number {
  let lo=0, hi=nums.length;
  while (lo<hi) {
    const mid=lo+Math.floor((hi-lo)/2);
    if (nums[mid]<target) lo=mid+1; else hi=mid;
  }
  return lo; // first index where nums[index] >= target
}
// Find right boundary (last occurrence / upper bound)
function upperBound(nums: number[], target: number): number {
  let lo=0, hi=nums.length;
  while (lo<hi) {
    const mid=lo+Math.floor((hi-lo)/2);
    if (nums[mid]<=target) lo=mid+1; else hi=mid;
  }
  return lo; // first index where nums[index] > target
}
// Binary search on answer — when result is monotonic
function binarySearchOnAnswer(lo: number, hi: number, feasible: (mid:number)=>boolean): number {
  while (lo<hi) {
    const mid=lo+Math.floor((hi-lo)/2);
    if (feasible(mid)) hi=mid; else lo=mid+1;
  }
  return lo;
}
```

## 3. Binary Search Variants
```typescript
// Search in Rotated Sorted Array (LC 33)
function searchRotated(nums: number[], target: number): number {
  let lo=0, hi=nums.length-1;
  while (lo<=hi) {
    const mid=lo+Math.floor((hi-lo)/2);
    if (nums[mid]===target) return mid;
    if (nums[lo]<=nums[mid]) { // left half is sorted
      if (nums[lo]<=target && target<nums[mid]) hi=mid-1;
      else lo=mid+1;
    } else { // right half is sorted
      if (nums[mid]<target && target<=nums[hi]) lo=mid+1;
      else hi=mid-1;
    }
  }
  return -1;
}
// Find minimum in rotated sorted array (LC 153)
function findMin(nums: number[]): number {
  let lo=0, hi=nums.length-1;
  while (lo<hi) {
    const mid=lo+Math.floor((hi-lo)/2);
    if (nums[mid]>nums[hi]) lo=mid+1; else hi=mid;
  }
  return nums[lo];
}
```

## 4. Counting Sort & Radix Sort
```typescript
// Counting sort — O(n+k) where k is value range
function countingSort(arr: number[], max: number): number[] {
  const count = new Array(max+1).fill(0);
  for (const n of arr) count[n]++;
  const result: number[] = [];
  for (let i=0;i<=max;i++) while(count[i]-->0) result.push(i);
  return result;
}
```

## 5. Sorting Algorithm Comparison
| Algorithm | Best | Average | Worst | Space | Stable |
|-----------|------|---------|-------|-------|--------|
| Quicksort | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n²) | O(log n) | No |
| Mergesort | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n) | Yes |
| Heapsort | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(1) | No |
| Timsort (JS .sort) | O(n) | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n) | Yes |
| Counting sort | O(n+k) | O(n+k) | O(n+k) | O(k) | Yes |
| Radix sort | O(nk) | O(nk) | O(nk) | O(n+k) | Yes |
| Bubble sort | O(n) | O(n²) | O(n²) | O(1) | Yes |

## 6. Binary Search on Answer Template
Whenever the answer is monotonic (feasible(x) → feasible(x+1)), binary search on the answer:
- Define feasible(mid) predicate
- Find smallest mid where feasible(mid) is true
- Boundary: lo=min_possible, hi=max_possible

## 7. Gotchas
- `lo + Math.floor((hi-lo)/2)` avoids integer overflow vs `(lo+hi)/2`
- Quicksort worst case: already sorted + last pivot → O(n²). Fix: random pivot
- Mergesort on linked lists: O(n log n) with O(1) extra space (link-based)
- Binary search: `lo<=hi` for exact search, `lo<hi` for boundary search
- `Array.sort()` in JS is NOT guaranteed stable before V8 7.0 (now Timsort — stable)
- Lower bound returns insertion point even if target not present
- For binary search on answer: always test feasibility on the SMALLER candidate

